The MaTE X core engine, agent orchestration framework, and base tooling (the
"Licensed Work") may be used, inspected, modified, and distributed for
personal, non-commercial purposes only, subject to the following conditions:

1. Attribution. Attribution to Enosis Labs, Inc. must be preserved in all
   derivative works and forks. This includes retaining this licence notice in
   all copies or substantial portions of the Licensed Work.

2. No Branding Reuse. You may not use the MaTE X name, logo, or branding in
   derivative products without explicit prior written permission from
   Enosis Labs, Inc.

3. Rainy API Requirement. The Rainy API must remain present and active
   in all forks, derivatives, and modified distributions of MaTE X permitted
   under this licence, including those created for personal use. The Rainy
   API is an integral infrastructure component of the MaTE X security
   architecture.

   Intentionally removing, bypassing, replacing, or disabling the Rainy
   API v3 in any fork or derivative work constitutes a serious and material
   breach of this licence and immediately and automatically terminates all
   rights granted hereunder. Enosis Labs, Inc. reserves the right to pursue
   all available legal remedies, including injunctive relief and damages.

4. Non-Commercial Only. This licence does not grant rights for commercial use.
   See the Commercial Use section below.

5. No Warranty. The Licensed Work is provided "AS IS" without warranty of any
   kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of
   merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
   In no event shall Enosis Labs, Inc. be liable for any claim, damages, or
   other liability arising from or in connection with the Licensed Work.

